In Mixed Reality people, not technology, are at the center of everything we do. The experiences we are enabling moves beyond screens and pixels, creating a new reality aimed at bringing us closer together. To get there, weâ€™re developing and incorporating groundbreaking technologies, from custom silicon to artificial intelligence to deliver the next generation of AR and VR experiences. The team delivers industry defining products like HoloLens, Altspace, Azure Mixed Reality services and Microsoft Mesh. 
Our team has people from a wide variety of backgrounds, identities, previous work histories, life experiences, and we are eager to maintain and grow that diversity. Our varied backgrounds and unique experiences enable us to be better at building the best solutions for our customers and make for dynamic and joyful collaborations with colleagues! 
If you are passionate about groundbreaking Mixed Reality products and want to work on a team dedicated to a culture of inclusion, growth mindset and collaboration, we need you!
 Responsibilities 
This role is for a technology focused leader within the Mixed Reality Strategy and Operations team. Our Mixed Reality product portfolio is broad spanning 1st Party and 3rd Party devices, cloud services and experiences. Our customers are equally diverse spanning consumers, majority of the fortune 500 companies and the public sector including defense customers. Our team is broadly geo distributed across Asia, Europe, North America, and Africa. Further we have fully embraced a hybrid model of work encouraging remote participation where possible and desired. 
To meet the needs of our broad portfolio, diverse customer footprint, and global team we are building a modern engineering system that enables developer productivity while ensuring the necessary compliance and security requirements are met. As the leader of engineering systems and compliance you will lead a cross functional team responsible for 
Building and running modern engineering system that ensures our global and hybrid workforce and collaboration partners are always productive 
Delivering world class infrastructure for internal development and program operations. 
Driving end-to-end operational security across all Mixed Reality programs 
Deliver and operationalize the Governance, Risk and Compliance (GRC) framework for Mixed Reality 
Qualifications 
10+ years of experience in systems engineering for the delivery of hardware and software products 
5+ years of experience as a general manager leading cross functional engineering teams of developers and program managers 
Familiarity with engineering systems, infrastructure, operational security and GRC 
Familiarity with Mixed Reality products and technologies 
BS or MS degree in Engineering 
#MixedReality 
Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include, but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: 
Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud background check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter. 
This position requires access to export-controlled commodities, technical data, technology, software, and services governed by the International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR). Due to contractual limitations and ITAR obligations associated with this role, U.S. citizenship, U.S. legal permanent resident status, or protected person status under 8 U.S.C. Â§ 1324b(a)(3) is required. 
